U.K. Treasury May Expand Tax Break to Existing Patents, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-10T01:10:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/u-k-treasury-may-expand-tax-break-to-existing-patents-ft-says.html
The U.K. Treasury is considering
expanding the scope of the so-called “patent box,” a 1.1
billion pound ($1.8 billion) tax break designed to attract
innovative industries to the country, to include existing
patents as well as new ones, the Financial Times reported,
citing a proposal by Treasury Exchequer Secretary, David Gauke,
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 